New Records: Zach Neto joined the 20-20 club with his 20th home run and 23 stolen bases, becoming the first Angels infielder in franchise history to produce a 20-20 season.
Key Match Events: Spencer Torkelson struck out swinging with the bases loaded in the eighth inning.
Zach Neto hit a milestone two-run home run in the fifth inning.
Mickey Moniak's RBI double in the fourth inning gave the Angels a 1-0 lead.
Jack Kochanowicz tossed six scoreless innings, lowering his ERA to 4.96.
Post-Match Reflections: A.J. Hinch commented on Ben Joyce's pitching, highlighting his velocity and aggressiveness.
Keider Montero reflected on his struggles with command during the game.
Zach McKinstry mentioned his improved consistency at the plate and better ball vision.
